{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}PDF2CSV{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<div class="px-4 py-5 my-5 text-center">
    <h1 class="display-5 fw-bold text-body-emphasis">PDF To CSV Converter</h1>
    <div class="col-lg-6 mx-auto">
        <p class="lead mb-4">
            To use the PDF To CSV Converter, set the Page Number to the correct page that your table exists on inside of the PDF. For example, if you have a 4 page PDF and the table of data you want extracted is on the <b>last page</b>, then you would set the page number to <b>4</b>. Once you have set your page number, upload the PDF file and click the Convert! button. The tool will do its work and give you a download option once the conversion is complete.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-6 mx-auto my-5 border rounded p-3">
        <form method="post" action="">
            <div class="mb-3 text-start">
                <label class="form-label" for="">What page number does your table exist on?</label>
                <input class="form-control" name="pages" value="1" type="number" placeholder="1" min="1">
            </div>
            <div class="mb-3 text-start">
                <input class="form-control" type="file">
            </div>
            <div class="mb-3 text-start">
                <button class="btn btn-primary disabled" type="submit">Convert!</button>
            </div>
        </form>
    </div>

</div>
{% endblock %}
